<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JAN 93 / Construction Contracts: Pounds 6.5m workload for WSJ
(Contractors)
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Contracts valued at Pounds 6.5m have been won by WSJ (CONTRACTORS), based in
Oswestry, on the Shropshire Welsh border.
In Shropshire, contracts totalling Pounds 3.4m have been secured and include
the Pounds 2.4m refurbishment of Shrewsbury's swimming centre and three
housing renovation schemes amounting to Pounds 1m, for clients Shrewsbury
and Atcham Borough Council, Oswestry Borough Council and Wrekin District
Council.
In Powys, projects include; a new industrial unit in Welshpool for the DBRW,
valued at Pounds 1.6m, and the construction of six bungalows for
Montgomeryshire District Council.
A further three projects in Clwyd, totalling Pounds 1m, are for the
following clients; Clwyd County Council, Wrexham Maelor Borough Council and
Delyn Borough Council.
