<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JAN 93 / Commodities and Agriculture: Thailand's rice growers face
water problem
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BANGKOK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THAILAND WILL face a severe water shortage within six months unless farmers
reduce the amount of land used to grow rice, government officials have
warned, reports Reuter from Bangkok.
Officials are concerned by reduced water levels in the two major Bhumibol
and Sirikit reservoirs which supply northern and central Thailand, including
Bangkok.
