<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Senior sells Davis Derby offshoot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Senior Engineering, the tubing, boilers and ductwork group, said yesterday
it had sold its Senior Davis Derby offshoot, which makes communications
equipment for hazardous environments, to Communication &amp; Control
Engineering.
The deal, for which terms were not disclosed, comes less than two months
after Senior said it would be withdrawing from the mining equipment business
due to the contraction of the UK coal industry.
The purchase trebles the size of CCE, a private company with 45 employees
which specialises in electrical equipment used in environments where fire is
a hazard. The combined company will have annual sales of about Pounds 8m.
</TEXT>
