<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Barclays sells stake in Israeli retail bank
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Barclays has sold its stake in an Israeli joint-venture retail bank for an
undisclosed sum.
The clearing bank said it sold its holding in Barclays Discount Bank - which
it set up with Israel Discount Bank in 1971 - to CP Holdings, a private
company controlled by Mr Bernard Schreier, a UK-based businessman. It said
the move was part of its strategy of concentrating resources on core
businesses.
