<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JAN 93 / UK Company News: TSW and UK Safety delay talks until March
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TELEVISION South West, the former ITV company, will in March re-open talks
about a reverse takeover with UK Safety Group, the Bristol-based specialist
shoe manufacturer.
TSW, shares in which were suspended at 29p yesterday, and UK Safety decided
that a full set of 1992 accounts would be needed for detailed negotiations
to get under way.
The group, replaced as the ITV broadcaster for the west of England by
Westcountry on January 1, expects to complete its final set of trading
accounts by the end of February.
A reverse takeover of UK Safety to give the shoe manufacturer a Stock
Exchange listing is the most likely future for TSW, although a liquidation
has not been ruled out.
An auction of remaining equipment will be held in April and attempts will be
made to sell the Plymouth headquarters site. Because of the depressed state
of the property market short-term lets are more likely.
TSW's assets include a tiny, but valuable stake in Astra, the
Luxembourg-based satellite system.
</TEXT>
