First prize for complicated erratum of 1993 awarded to Channel Four TV - or,
to be absolutely correct, its diary department.
'The Channel's Week 1 starts on 4th January and not during the extended week
53 as shown in the diary which conforms to a different computer numbering
system. This means that throughout this year Channel 4 personnel will be
working one week behind the week number shown at the top of each page of the
diary.'
Do not adjust your set.
