</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Only 18 per cent of UK small businesses have capitalised on Britain's
departure from the Exchange Rate Mechanism and the fall in sterling by
raising prices in foreign markets, according to a survey of 450 small
businesses carried out for Barclays Bank.
