FT  05 JAN 93 / Divided states seek UN entry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The new Czech Republic and Slovakia yesterday applied for UN membership,
writes AP from New York. UN officials said the two republics could be
admitted as early as mid-January. The new nations split their 74-year-old
homeland at midnight on new year's eve.
Macedonia, a former Yugoslav republic, is expected to apply for UN
membership early this year. Officials said they knew of no formal
application but Macedonian officials had said they intended to apply. Greece
has been trying to block Macedonia's recognition, saying it has usurped the
name of Greece's northern province.
Greece yesterday cautioned the UN Security Council's five permanent members
not to make a hasty decision, warning such recognition could undermine
regional stability.
