<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JAN 93 / Kenya to decide on Fresh elections
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL HOLMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
KENYA'S three main opposition leaders were last night meeting to decide
whether to pursue their demand for fresh elections, writes Michael Holman.
Leaders of FORD Kenya, FORD Asili and the Democratic party came under
growing pressure during the weekend from western diplomats. They were urged
to reconsider their call, which western governments regard as unwise and
impractical.
Instead, the parties have been advised to function as a powerful
parliamentary opposition.
Chief Emeka Anyaoku, the Commonwealth secretary-general, is due to arrive in
Nairobi today to help ease what has become a tense stand-off between
President Daniel arap Moi and the opposition.
'It is my earnest hope that government and political leaders will find ways
to work together for the peace, health, prosperity and unity of Kenya,'
Chief Anyaoku said in a statement.
</TEXT>
