<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JAN 93 / Construction Contracts: Leeds restoration project
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Historic Queens arcade (pictured right) in the centre of Leeds is being
restored to its Victorian splendour under a Pounds 2.7m contract awarded to
JOHN LAING CONSTRUCTION by the Arcade's owners, Co-operative Insurance.
In order to minimise disruption and ensure business as usual, Laing will be
holding regular liaison meetings with traders throughout the 45-week
contract.
Work involves constructing shop units behind the retained facade at the
Briggate end of the arcade. These will replace the recently demolished
structure.
In the the arcade itself the cast iron railings and balcony are to be
carefully restored, the roof re-glazed and the terrazzo flooring replaced.
The fire protection will be upgraded and all the shop fronts and elevations
restored to their former glory. Work is due to be finished in October.
</TEXT>
