<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JAN 93 / Life in the Single Market: Europe Today - The two faces of
contemporary France
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The French enter the single market as a nation of extremes. The political
agenda is dominated by divisions - between the old and the new, the rural
and the urban, the disadvantaged and the advantaged - and also by the
struggle of the old, centralised institutions that run the country to
resolve these divisions. One face of the country is the chic, educated
Parisian, who has prospered after almost a decade of socialism de lux. But
there is also France of the underclass - the under-privileged immigrants who
are struggling to eke out a living in the suburbs of Marseilles.
