FT  04 JAN 93 / Life in the single market: Europe Today - Collapse of
communism
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Entrepreneur Jan Kulczyk pictured with surplus Mig jet fighters. The
collapse of communism has left fledgling market economies on the EC's
eastern fringe, struggling to shake off the remnants of a state-controlled
economy. Amid the ruins of the Soviet bloc, men like Kulczyk see their
chance to forge trade between the east's food, raw materials and cheap
labour and the west's superior technology. The EC's single market offers
them the world's biggest trading bloc right on their doorstep - and with
everything to play for
