<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JAN 93 / Europe 1993: Europe Today - Europe's open market
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Spreading your professional wings abroad should be easier in Europe's open
market where qualifications gained at home are recognised across the
Community. In principle, a British teacher like the one above working in
Torremolinos, Spain, has been able to do so since 1990 when early single
market legislation fell into place. Most professional qualifications are now
recognised throughout the EC and additional measures enable free movement
for everyone from architects to hairdressers. However, in practice, many
professionals still face national and linguistic barriers, and find
transporting home-grown skills across borders less than straightforward.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>QRZ  European Economic Community (EC).
