<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JAN 93 / Observer: Facing the music
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The only glitch in the first of the Breakfast With Frost programmes on BBC
yesterday morning was that it ended with Britain's prime minister being cut
off while he was trying to answer the final question.
Surely the 9.15 start of the next children's programme could have been
delayed by a few seconds so that the PM could have been thanked for getting
up so early to give Sir David Frost's flagship show its first exclusive? The
Beeb, whose time keeping on its own news bulletins is hardly perfect, says
that the PM was in 'such good form' that he just carried on talking too
long. As for Sir David, dubbed by some snooty BBC types as their answer to
CNN's unctuous Larry King, he blames the music, or rather the lack of it.
Normally, the playing of the final signature tune is a cue for the
interviewee to shut up. Unfortunately, it was barely audible. Sir David
promises louder music in future.
